g.text: Beryllium oxides have been extensively studied due to their unique chemical properties and
important technological applications. Typically, in inorganic compounds beryllium is tetra-
hedrally coordinated by oxygen atoms. Herein based on results of in situ single crystal X-ray
diffraction studies and ab initio calculations we report on the high-pressure behavior of
